          "description": "I went to CityMD for severe oral pain and clearly explained that the roof of my mouth was raw and inflamed. I was first prescribed magic mouthwash, which no pharmacy was able to provide, making that prescription useless. I was then prescribed viscous lidocaine, which significantly worsened my symptoms, increasing both burning and irritation. This outcome was especially frustrating given how clearly I described my condition. While I understand treatments don\u2019t work the same for everyone, patient concerns and symptom details should be more carefully considered before defaulting to standard prescription. Overall unnecessary and disappointing experience, your better off asking Google and saving your money.",
